ssuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis is the first book to explore research on visiting friends and relatives (VFR). In many countries VFR is the largest single travel-related market and for some regional economies accounts for over half of all tourism flows. In assembling an international collection of quality VFR-related research the editors present the profiles, characteristics, opportunities and behaviours of VFR travel for the benefit of researchers, industry practitioners and educators. This holistic and international approach to understanding VFR travel provides a state of the art understanding of the context, dynamics and implications of VFR travel and will be an essential resource for postgraduate students, researchers and also practitioners.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aFamilies. 0aFriendship. 0aTourismxResearch. 0aTourismxSocial aspects. 4aTRAVEL & HOLIDAY. 4aTourism industry. 4aTravel with children / family holidays. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Hospitality, Travel & Tourism.2bisacsh  aVFR research.  aVFR tourism.  aVFR travel strategies.  aVFR travel.  aVFR.  adestination marketing.  afamily tourism.  atourism studies.  avisiting family and friends.  avisiting friends and relatives.1 aApostolakis, Alexandros, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBacker, Elisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBacker, Elisa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCave, Jenny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDwyer, Larry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGhaderi, Zahed, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffin, Tom, econtributo